README
Overview

This capsule contains the code and data required to reproduce the core analytical workflow described in the manuscript.

The recommended starting point for peer review is:
code/00_run_first.R

Running this script is sufficient to regenerate all panels of:
Figure 1
Figure 2
Figure 6
as reported in the manuscript.
All required intermediate datasets are already included in the data/ directory to ensure efficient execution during peer review.

Important note on figure layout

The final multi-panel figures presented in the manuscript were assembled and refined manually using Adobe Illustrator after generating individual panels via code.

Therefore:
This capsule reproduces all individual figure panels.
It does not reproduce the exact composite layout shown in the manuscript.
Minor aesthetic differences (e.g., font rendering, legend spacing, line width) may occur due to differences in package versions between the Code Ocean environment and the local desktop environment used during manuscript preparation.

The underlying data, analytical workflow, and scientific conclusions remain unchanged.

Capsule Structure

This capsule is organized into three main directories:
1) code/

Contains all R scripts used for detection, analysis, and plotting.
Recommended execution
Reviewers should run:
00_run_first.R

This script:
Sets the working directory
Creates a dedicated results folder
Sequentially executes the required scripts
Regenerates Figures 1, 2, and 6
No manual configuration is required.

Detection scripts

01_detect_AHW.R — Detect atmospheric heatwaves (AHWs)

02_detect_RHW.R — Detect riverine heatwaves (RHWs)

03_detect_ARCH.R — Detect atmospheric–riverine compound heatwaves (ARCH)

Sensitivity analysis

04_ARCH_sensitivity.R — ARCH sensitivity analysis 

Figure scripts

Figure 1:
Fig1_trend.R
Fig1_CE_map.R
Fig1_US_map.R

Figure 2:
Fig2a_CE_map.R
Fig2a_US_map.R
Fig2b.R
Fig2c.R
Fig2d.R

Figure 6:
Fig6_ARCH_example.R

Additional files

capsule.Rproj — RStudio project file

LICENSE

README

run — Code Ocean runtime entry

2) data/

Contains input datasets and precomputed intermediate results required by the scripts.

Key data components include:

temp_WT.csv — Water temperature data

Tmax_US_LamaH.csv — Atmospheric temperature data

AHW_attributes/ — Atmospheric heatwave attributes

RHW_attributes/ — Riverine heatwave attributes

ARCH_frequency_by_time_gap/ — ARCH frequency under different time-gap thresholds

attributes/ — Site-level and topographic attributes

LamaH/ — LamaH-related map datasets

All intermediate datasets required for figure reproduction are already included to reduce runtime during peer review.

3) results/

Contains outputs generated by running 00_run_first.R.

Directory structure:

results/
│
├── Fig1/
│   ├── Fig1_trend_plot.png
│   ├── Fig1_trend_summary.csv
│   ├── Fig1_CE_RHW_duration.png
│   ├── Fig1_CE_RHW_frequency.png
│   ├── Fig1_CE_RHW_intensity.png
│   ├── Fig1_US_RHW_duration.png
│   ├── Fig1_US_RHW_frequency.png
│   └── Fig1_US_RHW_intensity.png
│
├── Fig2/
│   ├── Fig2_map_CE_ARCH.png
│   ├── Fig2_map_US_ARCH.png
│   ├── Fig2b.png
│   ├── Fig2c.png
│   └── Fig2d.png
│
├── Fig6/
│   ├── Fig6_ARCH_main.png
│   └── Fig6_ARCH_zoom.png
│
├── Supplementary/
│   ├── ARCH_sensitivity_plot.png
│   └── ARCH_sensitivity_summary.csv
│
└── output/

All regenerated figures and summary outputs will be stored here.

Reproducibility Design

This capsule was structured to ensure clarity and reproducibility:

Explicit execution order (via 00_run_first.R)

No manual path configuration required

Precomputed intermediate data included

Independent script execution

Automatic output folder creation

Deterministic regeneration of main figures

Running 00_run_first.R is sufficient to reproduce the core results presented in the manuscript.